  "body": "For example, in our staged sync, we downloaded headers from 0 to 1000,\r\nWhen downloading bodies, we downloaded only from 0 to 100 and then there is a timeout.\r\n\r\nIn that case, we should go through the other stages of staged sync and only then go to the beginning.\r\n\r\nOtherwise, I got into issue when I was consistently 3-4 hours behind HEAD mostly because I couldn't download all the block bodies, got timeouts. But each time I did download a couple of blocks.\r\n",
